Beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, beating until very stiff and glossy. Fold in toasted coconut and almonds. Spoon into a 9 inch pie plate to form a shell. Bake at 350 degrees F (175 degrees) for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool. Fill with sliced peaches. Top with whipped cream and toasted coconut. Chill until ready to serve.